## Show recent (default)

Show the most recent 20 learnings, grouped by type.

Call `mcp__palantir-mini__pm_substrate_query` with `{ mode: "learn", limit: 20 }`. Present the returned
entries in a readable format, grouped by `type` (pattern / pitfall / preference /
architecture / tool / investigation). Each entry should show:

- `key` (short identifier)
- `insight` (one-sentence summary)
- `confidence` (1-10) if present
- `source` (user-stated / observed / inferred) if present

If the tool returns no entries, tell the user:

> No learnings recorded yet. As you use `/palantir-mini:pm-review`, `/palantir-mini:pm-ship`,
> `/palantir-mini:pm-investigate`, and other skills, palantir-mini will automatically
> capture patterns, pitfalls, and insights it discovers as `learning_captured` events
> in `events.jsonl`.

